WEBVTT

00:05.135 --> 00:08.617
Previously on
"Grey's Anatomy"...This dissection is
routine for me at this point.

00:08.660 --> 00:10.836
Bailey:
I need to know what happened.Dr. Schmitt started

00:10.880 --> 00:12.186
the dissection
instead of waiting.

00:12.229 --> 00:13.970
Time of death, 1:19.

00:14.014 --> 00:16.190
Why aren't you in pre-op?He has a low-grade fever.

00:16.233 --> 00:19.410
-Dr. Grey, he's hypotensive!
-Jo, you're right.

00:19.454 --> 00:21.064
I've been holding on to
a fairytale.

00:21.108 --> 00:22.761
We don't have to get married
now. I just need her, right?

00:22.805 --> 00:24.241
What happened?

00:24.285 --> 00:25.677
Winston:
The heart is a match for Farouk.

00:25.721 --> 00:27.114
It's a beautiful
and healthy heart.

00:27.157 --> 00:28.115
It's perfect.

00:28.158 --> 00:29.377
How are you holding up?

00:29.420 --> 00:31.031
If Farouk dies,
I go with him.

00:31.074 --> 00:32.728
-She is not alright.
-What's happening, Owen?

00:32.771 --> 00:34.469
[ Horn honks, tires squeal ]

00:34.512 --> 00:37.341
Nobody bloody move.
Take the cooler. Save Farouk.

00:37.385 --> 00:39.082
I gave Noah Young the drugs
that he needed to die,

00:39.126 --> 00:40.605
and I promised him that
I would give the same drugs

00:40.649 --> 00:42.346
to three
other dying soldiers.

00:42.390 --> 00:44.174
Move, before
it takes us both!

00:46.568 --> 00:49.310
♪♪

00:49.353 --> 00:55.316
[ Praying indistinctly ]

00:57.144 --> 00:59.842
[ Sighs ]

00:59.885 --> 01:00.973
Is that it?

01:01.017 --> 01:02.323
Yeah.

01:02.366 --> 01:04.151
You're sure?

01:04.194 --> 01:06.283
I've never been more sure
about anything in my life.

01:06.327 --> 01:08.285
And Heather knows?She does.

01:08.329 --> 01:10.809
We made a plan, and I can
take better care of Danny

01:10.853 --> 01:12.507
from the other side.

01:12.550 --> 01:14.900
[ Exhales sharply ]

01:14.944 --> 01:17.642
I feel good
about my life...

01:19.470 --> 01:21.385
...and I feel good
about where I'm going.

01:23.083 --> 01:25.955
I did my best, and...

01:25.998 --> 01:27.826
I think
that's pretty damn good.

01:31.134 --> 01:32.527
Yeah.

01:34.398 --> 01:35.660
Hey, Dr. Hunt?

01:36.922 --> 01:38.837
I don't want to abandon
the guys in my unit.

01:38.881 --> 01:41.144
They need your help, too.

01:41.188 --> 01:43.277
We...

01:43.320 --> 01:44.843
We need your help.

01:44.887 --> 01:46.541
Please.

01:46.584 --> 01:49.848
♪♪

01:49.892 --> 01:52.199
[ Breathing heavily ]

01:52.242 --> 01:53.635
[ Horn honks, tires squeal ]

01:53.678 --> 01:55.593
[ Groans ]

01:55.637 --> 01:57.465
[ Teddy screams,
glass shatters ]

01:57.508 --> 01:59.858
[ Groans, breathing heavily ]

01:59.902 --> 02:04.733
♪♪

02:04.776 --> 02:06.735
Here! I'm here!

02:06.778 --> 02:09.172
♪♪

02:09.216 --> 02:11.696
Meredith: The vagus nerve
is the longest and most complex

02:11.740 --> 02:13.220
of the cranial nerves.

02:13.263 --> 02:15.091
It transmits information

02:15.135 --> 02:16.745
to or from the surface
of the brain

02:16.788 --> 02:19.182
to tissues and organs
elsewhere in the body.

02:19.226 --> 02:22.751
Wait! Stop! Stop!

02:22.794 --> 02:24.144
Wait, wait!

02:24.187 --> 02:31.194
♪♪

02:31.238 --> 02:33.196
When a body sustains
an extended period

02:33.240 --> 02:34.850
of stress or trauma,

02:34.893 --> 02:38.332
the vagus nerve
becomes hyperactive.

02:38.375 --> 02:40.943
We think of stress and trauma
as primarily emotional...

02:40.986 --> 02:42.510
Richard:
Why didn't you wait?

02:42.553 --> 02:44.773
...but the real impact
is on the body.

02:44.816 --> 02:46.340
That's not
the Webber Method!

02:46.383 --> 02:47.776
When the vagus nerve
is triggered,

02:47.819 --> 02:49.952
it fights to slow the heart.

02:49.995 --> 02:55.044
♪♪

02:55.087 --> 02:56.828
Blood pressure drops,

02:56.872 --> 03:00.397
and you can experience nausea,
tunnel vision...

03:00.441 --> 03:03.183
[ High-pitched ringing ]

03:03.226 --> 03:06.664
...ringing in the ears,
low blood pressure,

03:06.708 --> 03:09.232
an irregular heartbeat.

03:09.276 --> 03:11.756
[ Alarms beeping ]

03:13.018 --> 03:16.108
And when the mind suffers,
the body suffers,

03:16.152 --> 03:18.981
and it can be difficult
to undo the damage.

03:19.024 --> 03:24.856
♪♪

03:24.900 --> 03:26.858
There was an accident.Winston:
Yeah, I heard.

03:26.902 --> 03:28.120
You okay?

03:28.164 --> 03:29.774
I will be
as long as the heart is.

03:29.818 --> 03:36.825
♪♪

03:36.868 --> 03:43.875
♪♪

03:43.919 --> 03:50.926
♪♪

03:50.969 --> 03:52.884
Ndugu?
The heart's bruised.

03:52.928 --> 03:54.321
It must have hit the side
of the cooler when the car --

03:54.364 --> 03:55.583
Can you still use it?

03:55.626 --> 03:57.280
[ Sighs ]

03:57.324 --> 04:02.981
♪♪

04:03.025 --> 04:04.287
Page Dr. Pierce.

04:04.331 --> 04:06.463
Woman: Please page Dr. Pierce
to OR 3.

04:06.507 --> 04:07.508
♪♪

04:21.348 --> 04:23.088
Amelia: [ Muffled ] Owen.

04:23.132 --> 04:24.525
[ Horn blares ]

04:24.568 --> 04:26.178
Owen, can you hear me?

04:26.222 --> 04:27.571
Owen: Hayes, I already
have the meds. Okay?!

04:27.615 --> 04:28.572
Aah!

04:28.616 --> 04:30.095
It's me. It's Amelia.

04:30.139 --> 04:31.183
Link is here, too.

04:31.227 --> 04:32.533
[ Groaning ]

04:32.576 --> 04:33.969
There you are.

04:34.012 --> 04:36.232
You were in an accident.
Do you remember?

04:36.276 --> 04:38.539
They gave you morphine on
the way here for the pain.
You're in trauma one.

04:38.582 --> 04:40.497
I know your leg hurts, but can
you wiggle your toes?

04:40.541 --> 04:41.977
Feel anything?

04:42.020 --> 04:43.718
Good. Okay.
Can you feel this?

04:43.761 --> 04:45.546
A little.Good. That's good.

04:45.589 --> 04:47.330
We are gonna get you scanned
and we're gonna get you into --

04:47.374 --> 04:50.290
Amelia. Amelia.
Teddy. Farouk's heart?

04:50.333 --> 04:51.943
Teddy's okay.
She's outside.

04:51.987 --> 04:53.467
Farouk is in surgery.
They got the heart here in time.

04:53.510 --> 04:55.512
Okay. Hayes?

04:55.556 --> 04:57.862
I haven't seen him, but
I will see what I can find out.

04:57.906 --> 04:59.516
Amelia.

04:59.560 --> 05:01.562
Don't tell Megan
that I'm hurt, okay?

05:01.605 --> 05:03.085
Owen --
Please.

05:03.128 --> 05:05.870
Not until after
Farouk's alright. Please.

05:07.568 --> 05:09.091
Amelia: Teddy.

05:09.134 --> 05:10.832
Do you need to sit down?

05:10.875 --> 05:12.094
Is he...?He's in a lot of pain,

05:12.137 --> 05:13.617
which right now
is a good thing.

05:13.661 --> 05:15.619
Preliminary assessment
shows extensive fractures

05:15.663 --> 05:17.142
to the left leg.His neuro exam?

05:17.186 --> 05:19.144
He's conscious,
and he's following commands.

05:19.188 --> 05:21.451
His motor and sensory exams
seem to be intact.

05:22.365 --> 05:23.758
Will he walk again?

05:23.801 --> 05:25.716
We'll know a lot more
after a scan.

05:27.109 --> 05:28.676
Teddy, he's alive.

05:30.112 --> 05:32.375
He's still here.

05:32.419 --> 05:33.637
You can go in and see him.

05:36.684 --> 05:37.728
Has anyone
checked youout yet?

05:37.772 --> 05:40.949
I'm fine. I'm --
I-I just, um...

05:40.992 --> 05:43.908
I just...

05:43.952 --> 05:46.650
I think I need a minute.
I-I'm not sure I...

05:46.694 --> 05:48.173
I just --
I-I need a minute.

05:48.217 --> 05:49.610
You got it.

05:54.615 --> 05:55.877
You should get
checked out, Teddy.

05:55.920 --> 05:57.400
He got me
out of the car first,

05:57.444 --> 06:00.751
and I went to call
for help and...

06:00.795 --> 06:02.840
and then I-I heard
the car fall,

06:02.884 --> 06:06.322
and I rode all the way here
with Farouk's heart in my hands,

06:06.366 --> 06:08.411
and I --
I thought Owen was dead.

06:08.455 --> 06:10.457
And it's just -- I feel like
my insides are like, lead,

06:10.500 --> 06:14.461
or like, you know, like --
like ice, and I just --

06:14.504 --> 06:17.638
I just need them to thaw
before I-I go --

06:17.681 --> 06:19.074
before I go inside
and see him.

06:19.117 --> 06:20.510
You've gone hard.

06:20.554 --> 06:22.338
Your nervous system
is protecting you.

06:22.382 --> 06:25.036
But he is alive.

06:25.080 --> 06:27.082
And he needs to see you.

06:27.125 --> 06:28.562
I know that.

06:30.477 --> 06:35.525
♪♪

06:35.569 --> 06:37.266
[ Owen groans ]

06:37.309 --> 06:39.442
[ Monitor beeping ]

06:39.486 --> 06:45.143
♪♪

06:45.187 --> 06:46.797
[ Groans ]

06:46.841 --> 06:48.364
Hi, Teddy.

06:50.061 --> 06:51.933
I thought you were gone.

06:51.976 --> 06:54.326
[ Exhales sharply ]

06:54.370 --> 06:55.850
Me too.

06:59.331 --> 07:01.290
Can you come over here,
please?

07:02.465 --> 07:04.206
[ Crying ]

07:04.249 --> 07:05.686
Hey.

07:07.601 --> 07:09.646
I'm still here.
[ Groaning ]

07:11.518 --> 07:13.041
[ Crying ]

07:13.084 --> 07:14.434
[ Speaking indistinctly ]

07:15.957 --> 07:18.089
I love you.
I know.

07:18.133 --> 07:20.396
Woman on P.A.:
Dr. Radford to 2-6-2-2.

07:20.440 --> 07:22.137
Hey.

07:22.180 --> 07:24.356
I think we just do a pan scan
and cover all our bases.

07:24.400 --> 07:26.924
I don't want to take a chance
of being blindsided in the OR.

07:26.968 --> 07:29.840
Couldn't agree more.
No one likes being blindsided.

07:31.146 --> 07:32.452
Link?

07:32.495 --> 07:34.105
Dr. Goldberg to the ICU.

07:34.149 --> 07:35.672
Link, are you alright?

07:35.716 --> 07:37.587
[ Sighs ]

07:37.631 --> 07:39.937
Link, Owen means a lot to me,
to everyone,

07:39.981 --> 07:41.461
so whatever is
going on with you --

07:41.504 --> 07:42.636
I have work to do.

07:42.679 --> 07:44.812
I'll, uh, meet you
in radiology.

07:46.814 --> 07:49.033
Richard: This is not about
the Webber Method, Bailey!

07:49.077 --> 07:51.383
It's about one surgeon --
one surgeon who overstepped.

07:51.427 --> 07:53.037
If we canceled
a teaching method

07:53.081 --> 07:54.865
every time a surgeon
made a mistake, there wou--

07:54.909 --> 07:58.390
Bailey: A preventable mistake.
It was preventable.

07:58.434 --> 08:00.741
I am suspending
the Webber Method

08:00.784 --> 08:02.960
immediately
and indefinitely.

08:03.004 --> 08:04.962
You absolutely will not.
I won't accept it.

08:05.006 --> 08:06.790
Now, you may be
the chief of this hospital,

08:06.834 --> 08:08.313
but I'm the chief
of chiefs.

08:08.357 --> 08:10.011
I will call
the medical board, Richard.

08:10.054 --> 08:12.666
You want to pull rank on me?
I will report you!

08:12.709 --> 08:14.015
Bailey!There should have been

08:14.058 --> 08:16.191
an attending
in that room!

08:16.234 --> 08:18.802
I am done arguing!

08:20.282 --> 08:24.242
Schmitt, stop wasting water.
Your hands are clean.

08:24.286 --> 08:30.118
♪♪

08:30.161 --> 08:31.336
Maggie: I don't know.

08:31.380 --> 08:33.338
[ Sighs ]
I don't think so.

08:33.382 --> 08:35.602
Winston: If we don't do this,
we have to put him back on ECMO,

08:35.645 --> 08:37.342
with risks of him bleeding

08:37.386 --> 08:39.910
or throwing a clot
causing a stroke, or worse.

08:39.954 --> 08:41.608
I don't know if he could
survive long enough
to get another heart.

08:41.651 --> 08:42.913
And if this heart fails

08:42.957 --> 08:44.741
because it was bouncing
around a cooler,

08:44.785 --> 08:47.178
he goes into
immediate cardiac arrest.

08:47.222 --> 08:48.789
[ Breathes deeply ]

08:48.832 --> 08:50.399
You called me here
for my opinion,

08:50.442 --> 08:52.532
and I think you need to wait
for a new heart.

08:55.056 --> 08:57.580
Okay, everyone.
Let's incise the right atrium.

08:57.624 --> 08:58.799
Dr. Ndugu --

08:58.842 --> 09:00.888
Dr. Pierce,
I know the risks,

09:00.931 --> 09:04.674
but it is a miraclethat Hunt
and Altman and Hayes are alive.

09:04.718 --> 09:06.894
It's a miracle that this heart
is in front of us right now.

09:06.937 --> 09:08.896
And it is a miracle that
we have the privilege

09:08.939 --> 09:12.726
to see if it will beat inside
Farouk's chest, bruised or not.

09:12.769 --> 09:17.295
So I'm gonna take the miracle
and trust my gut.

09:17.339 --> 09:19.994
And I'm asking you to help me
do this quickly and well.

09:22.910 --> 09:23.737
Okay.

09:27.784 --> 09:29.264
Scalpel.

09:29.307 --> 09:34.704
♪♪

09:40.754 --> 09:43.974
Nick: What do you mean
he lied?He had a bowel obstruction

09:44.018 --> 09:45.323
and he tried to hide
the pain from us

09:45.367 --> 09:46.934
until it got so bad
he nearly perfed.

09:46.977 --> 09:48.283
He was septic.
I almost lost him on the table.

09:48.326 --> 09:50.111
What an idiot.

09:50.154 --> 09:51.678
"Idiot" doesn't begin
to describe it.

09:51.721 --> 09:54.115
"Megalomaniac" maybe.[ Chuckles ]

09:54.158 --> 09:55.507
Hey. You know what?

09:55.551 --> 09:56.900
I've got a crazy idea.Yeah?

09:56.944 --> 09:58.772
There's a jet leaving
for Seattle,

09:58.815 --> 10:00.600
a critical care transport.

10:00.643 --> 10:02.602
I'm not -- I'm not working,
so I wasn't gonna go,

10:02.645 --> 10:03.690
but now I'm thinking...

10:03.733 --> 10:05.169
I don't know --
I hitch a ride

10:05.213 --> 10:06.736
and take you out
to drown your sorrows.

10:06.780 --> 10:08.912
Seriously? You hate this idea?

10:08.956 --> 10:10.914
I love this idea.[ Chuckles]

10:10.958 --> 10:13.351
Okay. In that case,
I gotta go.

10:13.395 --> 10:15.049
[ Beep ]

10:15.092 --> 10:17.573
[ Siren wails in distance ]

10:18.879 --> 10:22.230
Hey. Hayes,
what happened to your head?

10:22.273 --> 10:24.275
There was, uh...

10:24.319 --> 10:25.450
There was an accident.

10:25.494 --> 10:26.887
What kind of accident?

10:26.930 --> 10:28.932
[ Sighs ]

10:28.976 --> 10:30.673
My whole life...

10:30.717 --> 10:33.067
[ Clears throat ]

10:33.110 --> 10:36.679
My whole bloody life
flashed before my eyes.

10:36.723 --> 10:40.944
I saw Abigail and...

10:40.988 --> 10:42.293
my boys and...

10:42.337 --> 10:43.686
[ Sniffles ]

10:43.730 --> 10:46.210
It was just a lot.
It was a lot.

10:47.690 --> 10:49.910
Have you been checked out?I'm fine. I'm fine.

10:49.953 --> 10:52.521
Well, I'll be the judge of that.
Let's go inside. Come on.

10:52.564 --> 10:56.481
♪♪

10:56.525 --> 10:57.961
[ Sighs ]

11:01.530 --> 11:02.966
Pupils look good.

11:04.794 --> 11:06.187
Was there any
loss of consciousness?

11:06.230 --> 11:08.668
No.
I'm alright, Grey.

11:08.711 --> 11:11.148
Scale of one to ten,
how bad does your head hurt?

11:11.192 --> 11:12.672
It doesn't hurt.

11:14.761 --> 11:17.459
Just let me take
your blood pressure,

11:17.502 --> 11:19.504
and then we can agree
that you're okay.

11:23.813 --> 11:25.685
What's your opinion
on mercy killings?

11:25.728 --> 11:27.599
Whoa.
You've gone dark.

11:27.643 --> 11:29.253
No, I'm serious.

11:29.297 --> 11:31.212
What is your opinion
on mercy killings?

11:31.255 --> 11:32.430
And not on me.

11:34.519 --> 11:36.130
I believe in
death with dignity,

11:36.173 --> 11:38.045
if that's what
you're asking me.

11:38.088 --> 11:39.786
No, I'm asking what
you would think of a doctor

11:39.829 --> 11:41.831
who took that decision
into his own hands,

11:41.875 --> 11:43.920
who killed a man,
a man who wanted to die,

11:43.964 --> 11:46.749
a man who was gonna
die soon anyway.

11:46.793 --> 11:49.360
I would say
first do no harm.

11:49.404 --> 11:51.232
Yeah.
That's what I thought.

11:55.018 --> 11:56.846
Something
you want to tell me?

11:58.979 --> 12:00.850
Listen.

12:00.894 --> 12:03.461
Altman and Hunt
were in that car with me.

12:03.505 --> 12:05.376
Hunt was hurt.
How badly?

12:05.420 --> 12:07.509
Bad enough he might need
a great general surgeon.

12:09.119 --> 12:11.121
I came
as soon as I heard.

12:11.165 --> 12:12.296
What are
we looking at?

12:12.340 --> 12:13.907
L1 burst fracture.

12:13.950 --> 12:15.865
We'll need to go in
and remove any bone fragments

12:15.909 --> 12:17.911
before stabilizing it
with a cage.

12:17.954 --> 12:19.086
Open femoral fracture
needs a wash-out,

12:19.129 --> 12:20.652
and we'll use a nail
to fixate it.

12:20.696 --> 12:22.785
Left leg also has
a tibial plateau fracture.

12:22.829 --> 12:24.395
We'll have to wait a few days
for the swelling to go down

12:24.439 --> 12:25.396
before repairing it.

12:25.440 --> 12:26.833
Is that a splenic lac?

12:26.876 --> 12:28.704
Richard: Yeah,
looks like a Grade One.

12:28.748 --> 12:30.010
Let's monitor it
with labs.

12:30.053 --> 12:31.359
Yeah, the leg's
in much worse shape.

12:31.402 --> 12:33.361
You think he'll be able
to walk again?

12:33.404 --> 12:34.841
The sooner we get in,
the sooner we'll know.Shepherd?

12:34.884 --> 12:36.843
There is some retropulsion
into the spinal canal.

12:36.886 --> 12:39.933
But he's got some movement and
feeling, which is a good sign,

12:39.976 --> 12:41.804
but we'll have to get in quick,
and we'll need to be perfect.

12:41.848 --> 12:43.719
Perfect
or he's paralyzed?

12:43.763 --> 12:44.938
Yeah.

12:46.853 --> 12:49.116
Richard: Okay. Whatever OR
you need, it's yours.

12:49.159 --> 12:50.813
What about Schmitt?What about him?

12:50.857 --> 12:52.554
He's the best resident.
Can we have him?

12:52.597 --> 12:54.948
Schmitt's unavailable.[ Door opens ]

12:54.991 --> 12:56.253
Do you want me?You want to be
our resident?

12:56.297 --> 12:57.733
Well, I'm just saying,
if you need hands.

12:57.777 --> 12:59.604
Mer, we got him,
but if that changes,

12:59.648 --> 13:01.302
you'll be our first call.Okay.

13:01.345 --> 13:02.869
Our patient is awake.
I have to go yell at him.

13:02.912 --> 13:04.914
I'm here
if you need me, okay?

13:04.958 --> 13:06.829
[ Door opens ]

13:06.873 --> 13:09.658
Woman: Total room disinfection
in process.

13:11.138 --> 13:13.401
You're supposed to be
writing an operative report.

13:17.144 --> 13:18.885
Hey, I don't know what you think
you're scrubbing in on,

13:18.928 --> 13:19.929
but don't.

13:19.973 --> 13:22.105
You're in no condition.

13:22.149 --> 13:24.804
Total room disinfection
in process.

13:27.023 --> 13:28.808
Look, a surgeon
who's never lost a patient

13:28.851 --> 13:30.897
hasn't done enough surgeries.

13:30.940 --> 13:34.552
It happens,
even to the best of us.

13:34.596 --> 13:36.163
[ Cellphone buzzes ]

13:38.426 --> 13:40.123
[ Sighs ]

13:40.167 --> 13:41.690
Take a break, Schmitt.

13:41.733 --> 13:45.085
Take a walk,
feel your feelings...

13:45.128 --> 13:46.608
and then write that report.

13:48.131 --> 13:50.220
[ Door opens ]

13:50.264 --> 13:51.874
I'll start on
your burst fracture,

13:51.918 --> 13:53.615
and then Link and Nico
will start in

13:53.658 --> 13:54.921
on your femoral fracture.The other way around.

13:54.964 --> 13:56.966
Femoral fracture first,
then spine.

13:57.010 --> 13:58.663
We always start
with the spine.

13:58.707 --> 13:59.795
Yes, when the spinal fracture's
more unstable

13:59.839 --> 14:01.753
with motor and sensory deficits.

14:01.797 --> 14:04.017
In this instance, the leg is
shattered with an open wound

14:04.060 --> 14:06.628
and he has decreased
PT and DP pulses,

14:06.671 --> 14:08.238
so it takes priority
if he wants to keep it.

14:08.282 --> 14:09.936
Nico: We could
actually compromise here.

14:09.979 --> 14:12.112
We position Hunt on his side,
we both go in laterally --

14:12.155 --> 14:13.635
you in through
the lumbar spine,

14:13.678 --> 14:15.028
and I'll go in through
the side of the femur.

14:15.071 --> 14:17.247
We do the repairs
simultaneously.

14:18.727 --> 14:20.511
Owen, the risks here are
you lose your leg

14:20.555 --> 14:22.774
or you lose the ability
to use your legs.

14:22.818 --> 14:24.080
I really think
that we want to --

14:24.124 --> 14:25.560
-Where's Hayes?
-Hayes?

14:25.603 --> 14:27.083
Yeah.
I need to see him.

14:27.127 --> 14:28.911
We need to get you into the OR
as soon as possible.

14:28.955 --> 14:30.913
Owen, listen. You can talk
to Hayes after your surgery.

14:30.957 --> 14:33.916
No, no. No. No. I need to talk
to Hayes, and it can't wait.

14:35.962 --> 14:37.702
I will see if he can
meet you in pre-op.

14:39.443 --> 14:40.792
Okay.

14:40.836 --> 14:43.360
And we will go in
simultaneously.

14:43.404 --> 14:51.412
♪♪

14:51.455 --> 14:53.675
Okay?

15:00.116 --> 15:03.641
Ndugu.
We know anything yet?

15:03.685 --> 15:04.947
I'd like to give his mother
an update.There's no way to know
just yet.

15:04.991 --> 15:06.601
We still have a couple
more vessels to anastomose.

15:06.644 --> 15:09.169
Winston:
But for what it's worth...

15:09.212 --> 15:11.214
I have a good feeling.

15:11.258 --> 15:16.480
♪♪

15:16.524 --> 15:21.964
♪♪

15:22.008 --> 15:25.576
Woman on P.A.: Dr. Sellers.
Dr. Mari Sellers. 4-6-1-9.

15:25.620 --> 15:27.100
[ Owen groans ]

15:27.143 --> 15:28.579
Dr. Mari Sellers. 4-6-1-9.

15:28.623 --> 15:30.930
My God. Look at you.

15:30.973 --> 15:32.583
[ Sighs ]
Could have been much worse.

15:32.627 --> 15:34.063
Yeah.
Could have been me.

15:34.107 --> 15:36.761
[ Chuckles ]

15:36.805 --> 15:38.111
[ Sighs ]

15:38.154 --> 15:40.417
Thank you, Hunt.

15:40.461 --> 15:42.245
I don't know
what else to say.

15:42.289 --> 15:44.073
Thank you.

15:44.117 --> 15:46.162
You could thank me by
forgetting what I told you.

15:46.206 --> 15:47.294
[ Sighs ]

15:49.383 --> 15:52.299
If I do that...

15:52.342 --> 15:54.605
then I'm an accessory
to a crime.

15:54.649 --> 15:57.304
Hayes, Noah was dying.
You know that.

15:57.347 --> 15:59.088
He qualified for
physician assisted death.

15:59.132 --> 16:00.611
Then why do you want me
to forget about it?

16:00.655 --> 16:02.570
'Cause his friends
don't come from states

16:02.613 --> 16:04.528
that allow
death with dignity.

16:04.572 --> 16:07.923
I made him a promise,
and he made them a promise.

16:07.967 --> 16:10.708
So you stole drugs and plan
to pass them out like candy?

16:10.752 --> 16:12.362
I plan to show
those soldiers

16:12.406 --> 16:14.016
the respect
that our country hasn't.

16:14.060 --> 16:16.410
I plan to keep my promise
to those men, okay?

16:16.453 --> 16:18.412
You saved my life, and I need
to spend what's left of it

16:18.455 --> 16:20.892
looking after my boys.

16:20.936 --> 16:23.156
I can't go to prison.That's not gonna happen.

16:23.199 --> 16:25.723
You stole life-ending drugs
that you plan to dispense

16:25.767 --> 16:28.813
to men who do not qualify.

16:28.857 --> 16:30.772
Come forward,

16:30.815 --> 16:32.469
tell Bailey what you've done,
what you plan to do next.

16:32.513 --> 16:33.731
The longer you hold
this secret inside,

16:33.775 --> 16:35.037
the worse it's gonna get.

16:35.081 --> 16:36.996
Tell the truth
so I don't have to.

16:37.039 --> 16:38.867
I fell off of a cliff
so you didn't have to.

16:38.910 --> 16:40.912
If not prison,
I'd almost certainly

16:40.956 --> 16:42.914
lose my license
to practice medicine

16:42.958 --> 16:45.265
for knowing about this
and failing to report it.Hayes, come on.

16:45.308 --> 16:47.441
Hunt, I'm grateful to you
for getting me out of that car,

16:47.484 --> 16:49.965
but I can't make you
any promises.

16:50.009 --> 16:51.793
I need to
think this through.

16:51.836 --> 16:53.229
[ Sighs ]

16:59.888 --> 17:02.412
Hey. Farouk's heart?We don't know yet.

17:02.456 --> 17:04.414
Okay. Thank you.

17:04.458 --> 17:09.637
♪♪

17:09.680 --> 17:10.942
Hey.

17:10.986 --> 17:16.818
♪♪

17:20.300 --> 17:22.084
[ Loud rattling ]

17:22.128 --> 17:24.434
[ Groans ]

17:24.478 --> 17:26.132
I'm sorry.No.

17:26.175 --> 17:27.524
No, I'm not sorry?

17:27.568 --> 17:29.657
I'm not interested
in your apology.

17:29.700 --> 17:31.093
I'm honestly not
super into it, either.

17:31.137 --> 17:33.530
Dr. Bartley worked two years
on this protocol,

17:33.574 --> 17:35.880
and you nearly ruined it.

17:35.924 --> 17:37.230
S-Stupid.

17:37.273 --> 17:38.883
Way worse than stupid.

17:38.927 --> 17:42.104
David, you were septic.
You almost died.

17:42.148 --> 17:45.107
We don't have another patient
with Parkinson's

17:45.151 --> 17:47.892
who will volunteer to let us
experiment on his brain,

17:47.936 --> 17:51.113
and even if we did,
the FDA only approved you.

17:51.157 --> 17:52.854
You're it.

17:52.897 --> 17:55.857
Our time is
a non-renewable resource.

17:55.900 --> 17:57.467
I have children
here in Seattle

17:57.511 --> 18:00.340
that I am missing days with
that I will not get back.

18:00.383 --> 18:03.430
So if you pull a stunt
like this again, I will quit,

18:03.473 --> 18:06.998
and if I quit,
the FDA will kill this project.

18:07.042 --> 18:09.914
And then I will have wasted
two years of Dr. Bartley's time.

18:09.958 --> 18:12.308
We'll get over it,
but you won't,

18:12.352 --> 18:14.136
because you will die
with Parkinson's.

18:14.180 --> 18:15.311
Understood?

18:15.355 --> 18:17.183
Understood.

18:17.226 --> 18:21.448
♪♪

18:21.491 --> 18:22.753
[ Door closes ]

18:22.797 --> 18:24.364
Yeah.

18:24.407 --> 18:26.017
I'm walking out, too.

18:27.193 --> 18:28.716
But only 'cause
I need more coffee.

18:28.759 --> 18:30.892
[ Door opens ]

18:30.935 --> 18:38.552
♪♪

18:41.859 --> 18:44.210
Hey. Bailey told me
what happened.

18:44.253 --> 18:45.733
She thought you might
still be in here,

18:45.776 --> 18:47.430
so she sent me
to take you home.

18:47.474 --> 18:50.651
Levi, it's the worst,
and we've all been there.

18:53.044 --> 18:54.568
Levi, your hands!

18:55.569 --> 18:57.919
Levi. Okay.
You need to stop --

18:57.962 --> 18:59.312
[ Gasps ]

18:59.355 --> 19:00.617
Levi!

19:04.273 --> 19:06.754
[ Scrubbing continues ]

19:23.379 --> 19:24.728
Hayes: Megan.

19:27.166 --> 19:29.690
I wanted to give you an update.
Your mother said you were here.

19:31.300 --> 19:34.216
I came here to pray,
and I don't pray.

19:34.260 --> 19:37.654
But I came here to pray because
no one will tell me anything.

19:37.698 --> 19:38.873
No one's told me anything
for hours.

19:38.916 --> 19:40.527
I haven't seen Teddy.
I haven't seen Owen.

19:40.570 --> 19:42.268
I haven't seen you.

19:42.311 --> 19:44.705
No one will give me
an update.

19:46.489 --> 19:47.708
How bad is it?

19:49.536 --> 19:51.233
Megan,
I need to know your plan.

19:51.277 --> 19:53.104
[ Sighs ] What plan?

19:53.148 --> 19:55.194
I need to know your plan
for how not to kill yourself.

19:57.065 --> 19:59.241
Maybe it's medication.
Maybe it's inpatient treatment.

19:59.285 --> 20:01.200
Maybe it's just
talking to your family,

20:01.243 --> 20:04.028
letting them know how you feel
and then letting them take over.

20:04.072 --> 20:06.770
Whatever it is, I need to know
your plan for living.

20:15.126 --> 20:19.130
My wife died a few years back.
Did you know that?

20:19.174 --> 20:20.871
No.

20:20.915 --> 20:22.917
I tried to move on.
I couldn't.

20:22.960 --> 20:24.353
I blamed it
on my son's panic attacks,

20:24.397 --> 20:27.269
but the truth is...

20:27.313 --> 20:28.705
I'm not over Abigail.

20:31.317 --> 20:33.232
I don't know
if I'll ever get over her.

20:34.624 --> 20:36.191
I desperately don't want
to leave my boys,

20:36.235 --> 20:38.715
but I'm desperate
to see Abigail again.

20:38.759 --> 20:42.197
What I'm saying is,
I know how it feels

20:42.241 --> 20:45.896
to want to live
and not want to live.

20:45.940 --> 20:47.898
I know the depth
of that grief.

20:47.942 --> 20:49.900
I know the impulse
to want to leave the planet.

20:51.162 --> 20:53.730
But if I'm gonna
give you more bad news,

20:53.774 --> 20:58.996
I need to know that I'm not
handing you a bottle of pills...

20:59.040 --> 21:00.650
that I'm not
taking you out.

21:03.044 --> 21:04.393
[ Sniffles ]

21:04.437 --> 21:06.569
I took a sedative.
That helped.

21:09.442 --> 21:13.097
You can watch me
call my therapist.

21:13.141 --> 21:16.187
And I'll e-mail my psychiatrist
and CC you.

21:16.231 --> 21:18.886
Just please --
If you'll please just tell me.

21:18.929 --> 21:20.801
Tell me everything.

21:21.671 --> 21:23.369
There was an accident.

21:23.412 --> 21:25.545
Car went off the road.
The heart was bruised.

21:25.588 --> 21:27.503
Ndugu thinks
it's still functional,

21:27.547 --> 21:29.897
so they're working on Farouk
right now.

21:29.940 --> 21:31.507
Owen was injured.

21:31.551 --> 21:32.856
His injuries are not
life-threatening,

21:32.900 --> 21:33.944
but his leg was shattered.

21:33.988 --> 21:35.685
He is also in surgery.

21:37.121 --> 21:39.341
Wow. [ Chuckles ]

21:39.385 --> 21:40.777
When it rains, it pours, huh?

21:40.821 --> 21:42.692
Yeah.

21:42.736 --> 21:46.174
♪♪

21:46.217 --> 21:48.089
Alright.

21:48.132 --> 21:49.656
Let's make that call.
Have you got your phone?

21:49.699 --> 21:51.919
[ Breathes deeply ]

21:51.962 --> 21:53.224
Yeah.

21:53.268 --> 22:00.667
♪♪

22:00.710 --> 22:02.146
Hey.

22:02.190 --> 22:03.234
How's it going?

22:03.278 --> 22:04.714
Ahh.

22:04.758 --> 22:06.455
I can't imagine Owen Hunt

22:06.499 --> 22:08.588
unable to stand
over an operating table.

22:08.631 --> 22:11.025
Is that where we are?

22:11.068 --> 22:13.070
Eh, I don't know.
It's slow going.

22:15.464 --> 22:16.944
Heard about Schmitt?

22:16.987 --> 22:18.598
No.

22:18.641 --> 22:20.513
He had a tough loss.

22:20.556 --> 22:22.863
Young guy in his 20s.

22:22.906 --> 22:25.387
He bled out
in Schmitt's OR.

22:25.431 --> 22:28.869
And I should be comforting him,
but I am just so angry

22:28.912 --> 22:32.133
because he was at the
anastomosis with the stapler

22:32.176 --> 22:34.875
and he didn't wait
for the attending.Oh.

22:34.918 --> 22:36.572
Put too much traction
on the IMA,

22:36.616 --> 22:38.182
and it avulsed
at the aorta.

22:38.226 --> 22:41.621
Just hubris.
Just...pure and simple.

22:41.664 --> 22:43.405
I wouldn't have waited.

22:43.449 --> 22:46.452
If you had been teaching
this way when I started, I...

22:46.495 --> 22:48.410
would have been drunk
on it.

22:48.454 --> 22:50.281
Cristina wouldn't have waited.
Alex wouldn't have waited.

22:50.325 --> 22:52.283
O-Okay. I got it.
Thanks.

22:52.327 --> 22:53.894
I'm just saying --

22:53.937 --> 22:55.678
No, you're saying
that Bailey was right.

22:55.722 --> 22:58.028
You're saying we should kill
the Webber Method completely.

22:58.072 --> 23:00.161
No, that's not
what I'm saying.

23:00.204 --> 23:02.772
I'm...

23:02.816 --> 23:06.428
I am just saying
that I am...

23:06.472 --> 23:08.082
sorry for Schmitt.

23:08.125 --> 23:11.477
♪♪

23:11.520 --> 23:14.871
Amelia: Exposing the endplate.
Drill, please.

23:14.915 --> 23:17.352
Link:
Hold the drill for a second.
Nico's checking his anastomosis.

23:17.396 --> 23:18.788
Tell me when.

23:20.399 --> 23:22.662
[ Pulse whooshing ]

23:22.705 --> 23:25.055
Strong signal.
The primary repair worked.

23:25.099 --> 23:27.318
I'm not seeing any other
neuro-vascular issues.

23:27.362 --> 23:28.407
More irrigation,
please.

23:28.450 --> 23:30.452
Shepherd, go ahead.

23:30.496 --> 23:32.106
[ Drill whirring ]

23:33.499 --> 23:34.630
[ Whirring stops ]

23:34.674 --> 23:37.198
[ Monitor beeping ]

23:40.549 --> 23:42.290
[ Whirring resumes ]

23:46.207 --> 23:48.514
Can we clear the gallery,
please?

23:48.557 --> 23:50.124
What?
I need to focus.

23:50.167 --> 23:53.693
And I -- I'm asking
to clear the gallery.

23:55.738 --> 23:57.740
Can we clear the gallery,
please?!

24:03.050 --> 24:07.097
♪♪

24:07.141 --> 24:08.447
Amelia: Rongeur.

24:08.490 --> 24:10.013
Now to clean some
of this dead tissue.

24:10.057 --> 24:11.580
Nice work, Nico.
Now I need you to --

24:11.624 --> 24:12.929
Debride and then do
a wet-to-dry dressing.

24:12.973 --> 24:13.974
I got it.

24:14.931 --> 24:17.238
Owen,
we are almost done.

24:17.281 --> 24:21.155
♪♪

24:21.198 --> 24:23.679
Woman on P.A.:
Nurse Kaiser to the OR.

24:23.723 --> 24:26.160
Nurse Kaiser to the OR.

24:26.203 --> 24:27.727
-Oh! Sorry!
-Whoa. Whoa. You okay?

24:27.770 --> 24:30.120
Um, I need your help.
It's Levi.

24:30.164 --> 24:31.382
Our friend needs our help.

24:37.214 --> 24:39.695
-Oh, my God.
-Levi. It's been hours.

24:39.739 --> 24:41.088
You have to stop.

24:42.524 --> 24:45.875
Uh...Schmitt.

24:45.919 --> 24:49.705
I heard what happened, man,
and I've been there.

24:49.749 --> 24:51.446
The first patient I lost,
I went running.

24:51.490 --> 24:53.056
I went running
for five hours

24:53.100 --> 24:54.449
until my legs gave out
and my friends found me

24:54.493 --> 24:57.017
collapsed on the side of
the street, unable to move.

24:57.060 --> 24:58.888
I get it.
I know how you feel.

24:58.932 --> 25:01.456
But you have to stop, okay?

25:05.634 --> 25:07.593
Um, listen.

25:07.636 --> 25:09.420
Step back.

25:09.464 --> 25:12.511
Look, um...
It's gonna be okay.

25:12.554 --> 25:14.208
You have to
step back, though.

25:14.251 --> 25:16.253
And the water
will turn off.

25:16.297 --> 25:17.864
Just step back.

25:17.907 --> 25:19.300
I've got you, buddy.
It's alright.

25:19.343 --> 25:20.562
-No! [ Screaming ]
-It's alright. It's alright.

25:20.606 --> 25:22.651
-Levi.
-It's alright.

25:22.695 --> 25:23.783
-Watch out!
-It's alright. It's alright.

25:23.826 --> 25:25.175
[ Levi screaming ]Levi.

25:25.219 --> 25:26.655
It's okay.Alright.

25:26.699 --> 25:28.614
-It's okay, Levi.
-You're okay. You're okay.

25:28.657 --> 25:30.050
-It's alright.
-You're okay.

25:30.093 --> 25:31.138
-It's okay.
-Let him up.

25:31.181 --> 25:32.487
It's okay.

25:32.531 --> 25:34.663
[ Levi screaming ]

25:47.763 --> 25:49.025
I'll get him
up to the ICU.

25:49.069 --> 25:50.549
When do you want
the first post-op labs?

25:50.592 --> 25:52.159
Link:
As soon as he arrives.

25:52.202 --> 25:53.595
And I want them doing
regular neuro-vascular checks.

25:53.639 --> 25:55.292
Nico: Got it.

25:55.336 --> 25:57.251
Woman on P.A.:
Dr. Rymock to the Psych Unit.

25:57.294 --> 25:59.035
Dr. Rymock,
call the Psych Unit.

26:00.733 --> 26:02.517
You spent the day
punishing me

26:02.561 --> 26:04.388
because you saw me
kissing someone else?

26:04.432 --> 26:06.913
You brought all of that --
all of that into Owen's surgery.

26:06.956 --> 26:09.132
You don't think maybe
a conversation

26:09.176 --> 26:10.743
before we're cutting into
someone I love?

26:10.786 --> 26:13.615
Are you kidding me?
You think youget to be upset?

26:13.659 --> 26:15.182
Are you serious?!

26:15.225 --> 26:17.967
I'm over here
piningfor you, Amelia,

26:18.011 --> 26:20.622
head-over-heels,
can't-think-straight pining,

26:20.666 --> 26:21.971
because you told me
you loved me.

26:22.015 --> 26:24.713
You told me
over and over and over.

26:24.757 --> 26:25.888
We were building a life
together,

26:25.932 --> 26:27.890
and suddenly, you say,
"No, thanks."

26:27.934 --> 26:30.153
And while I'm torturing myself
trying to convince myself

26:30.197 --> 26:31.981
that I don't need to be married,
I just need you.

26:32.025 --> 26:34.897
Since when?Since now. Since today.

26:34.941 --> 26:37.813
And I came to tell you this,
but instead, I find you

26:37.857 --> 26:41.164
kissing someone else
in the hospital where I work!

26:43.210 --> 26:45.342
You -- You just moved on.

26:45.386 --> 26:47.170
You just --
You just moved on

26:47.214 --> 26:48.650
like the last year and a half
didn't matter.

26:48.694 --> 26:50.521
Okay. I am not a person
who just moves on.

26:50.565 --> 26:52.654
I had to think and process

26:52.698 --> 26:54.308
and go through
every scenario in my head

26:54.351 --> 26:56.527
and every feeling in my body,
and it was exhausting.

26:56.571 --> 26:58.529
And you know that I spent
a year in A.A. meetings

26:58.573 --> 27:00.140
trying to figure out
what I needed,

27:00.183 --> 27:03.796
and you did not want to hear
that I was losing myself

27:03.839 --> 27:08.627
in something that I did not --
that I could not want.

27:08.670 --> 27:12.892
You demanded
that I marry you,

27:12.935 --> 27:14.589
and now once again,
you want to gaslight me

27:14.633 --> 27:16.765
into thinking
that I played you?

27:19.725 --> 27:21.204
[ Chuckles ]

27:21.248 --> 27:25.208
You keep using that word --
"gaslight."

27:25.252 --> 27:27.384
That's when you pretend that
someone else's experience,

27:27.428 --> 27:30.561
their -- their, uh, reality
isn't real, right?

27:30.605 --> 27:31.911
Like when you pretend that

27:31.954 --> 27:34.391
we didn't make
an amazing baby together,

27:34.435 --> 27:37.830
raise four kids, or love
each other really damn well.

27:39.745 --> 27:41.398
When you pretend that
we weren't in love

27:41.442 --> 27:44.445
because you're ready to move on
with some random woman.

27:44.488 --> 27:46.360
They're non-binary.

27:46.403 --> 27:49.189
[ Sarcastically ] Oh. Okay.
T-That makes it better.

27:55.325 --> 27:57.414
Congratulations.

27:57.458 --> 27:59.329
I hope you're really happy.

27:59.373 --> 28:07.686
♪♪

28:07.729 --> 28:09.078
Winston: Okay, everyone.

28:09.122 --> 28:10.645
We're gonna try
to get this heart going.

28:10.689 --> 28:11.820
If it doesn't beat,
I need everybody ready

28:11.864 --> 28:13.169
to go back on bypass.

28:16.782 --> 28:18.784
Okay.
Taking off clamp.

28:18.827 --> 28:24.224
♪♪

28:24.267 --> 28:29.838
♪♪

28:29.882 --> 28:31.231
Here we go.

28:31.274 --> 28:37.193
♪♪

28:37.237 --> 28:43.460
♪♪

28:43.504 --> 28:45.158
♪ I hear...

28:45.201 --> 28:47.464
Jo: You're gonna go home,
and you're gonna sleep

28:47.508 --> 28:50.859
and hydrate and eat if you can
and cry if you can,

28:50.903 --> 28:52.339
and, little by little,

28:52.382 --> 28:53.906
you will feel like
you can breathe again.

28:53.949 --> 28:55.734
[ Cellphone buzzes ]

28:55.777 --> 28:57.997
I have to take this.
Don't wrap it too tight.

28:58.040 --> 28:59.694
Hey.
Don't leave him alone.

28:59.738 --> 29:01.000
Call me if you need me.Yeah.

29:01.043 --> 29:03.916
♪ In the air

29:03.959 --> 29:06.701
What happened?
You okay?

29:06.745 --> 29:08.877
♪ Nothing is clear

29:08.921 --> 29:11.662
Hey.
What happened to him?

29:11.706 --> 29:15.014
Levi? What --
What is going on here?

29:15.057 --> 29:17.712
-Let's, um...
-Yeah, yeah. I got it.

29:17.756 --> 29:19.627
♪ Ahh-ahh

29:19.670 --> 29:21.542
Let's take a walk,
Nico.

29:21.585 --> 29:23.849
Yeah?

29:23.892 --> 29:25.589
♪ These secrets
sound like sirens ♪

29:25.633 --> 29:26.895
Nico:
What's going on?

29:26.939 --> 29:30.769
Alright, man.
We are done here.

29:30.812 --> 29:32.118
Everything's
gonna be alright.

29:32.161 --> 29:33.597
♪ Sound like sirens

29:33.641 --> 29:36.383
♪ But they never come

29:36.426 --> 29:40.082
♪ Ahhh

29:40.126 --> 29:42.868
♪♪

29:42.911 --> 29:46.088
♪ Ahhhh

29:46.132 --> 29:51.137
♪ Stand on edges
where fear is proud ♪

29:52.834 --> 29:56.359
♪ They don't like to be found

29:56.403 --> 29:59.406
His heart is beating,
and it's beating well, Megan.

29:59.449 --> 30:04.367
♪ Shadows flee
in the blackest night ♪

30:04.411 --> 30:06.587
[ Megan crying ]

30:06.630 --> 30:09.808
♪ Without me
they won't survive ♪

30:11.418 --> 30:12.941
♪ Ahhhh

30:12.985 --> 30:14.508
[ Megan laughs ]

30:14.551 --> 30:16.249
Thank you.
Thank you. Thank you.

30:17.206 --> 30:18.294
Thank you.

30:18.338 --> 30:20.819
♪ Ahhhh

30:22.168 --> 30:25.606
Dr. Ndugu made sure
the graft was perfect,

30:25.649 --> 30:26.694
and he'll be up any minute.

30:28.000 --> 30:29.784
What -- What about, uh, Owen?

30:29.828 --> 30:31.830
Is he out of surgery yet or...?

30:31.873 --> 30:34.528
We will get an update to you
as soon as we can.

30:34.571 --> 30:37.966
Right now, I just want you
to take this in.

30:38.010 --> 30:39.925
Farouk's heart
is beating in his chest.

30:39.968 --> 30:41.970
He's okay.

30:42.014 --> 30:45.756
And it's okay to --
to take in the miracle.

30:45.800 --> 30:47.889
♪ These secrets
sound like sirens ♪

30:47.933 --> 30:50.979
♪ But they never come

30:51.023 --> 30:57.725
♪♪

30:57.768 --> 31:04.471
♪♪

31:04.514 --> 31:11.260
♪♪

31:11.304 --> 31:18.093
♪♪

31:23.229 --> 31:26.188
[ Knock on door ]

31:26.232 --> 31:27.886
Dr. Bailey,
can I have a word?

31:27.929 --> 31:31.106
Bailey: Yeah, just let me --
Oh, your head.

31:31.150 --> 31:35.197
Uh, any update
on the Hunt family?

31:35.241 --> 31:37.591
Farouk's heart transplant
was a success.

31:37.634 --> 31:39.636
Oh. And Owen?

31:39.680 --> 31:42.683
I, uh...
I haven't heard.

31:42.726 --> 31:45.077
Well, I need him
to be okay.

31:45.120 --> 31:48.776
[ Sighs ] That family
has been through so much.

31:48.819 --> 31:51.213
They've lived
lives of service.

31:51.257 --> 31:54.173
The mother was an Army nurse.
Did you know that?

31:54.216 --> 31:56.827
No.
Whole military family.

31:56.871 --> 32:01.093
Owen Hunt is one of
the best men I know.

32:01.136 --> 32:05.314
He cares and he fights
and he...

32:05.358 --> 32:07.316
He's gonna be okay.

32:07.360 --> 32:09.971
I'm just gonna decide that
right now.

32:10.015 --> 32:12.974
Owen Hunt is gonna be okay!
You hear me?

32:13.018 --> 32:15.063
Oh, this day.
Did you hear about Schmitt?

32:15.107 --> 32:17.109
Dr. Bailey.

32:17.152 --> 32:18.458
I have to give you my notice.

32:18.501 --> 32:19.850
What?
I'm sorry.

32:21.287 --> 32:22.636
My kids,
they're not thriving here.

32:22.679 --> 32:24.116
They're not happy.

32:24.159 --> 32:25.073
We have to go.

32:26.161 --> 32:27.858
W-Where?

32:27.902 --> 32:29.208
Back to Ireland.

32:30.513 --> 32:32.428
[ Laughing ] O-kay.

32:32.472 --> 32:35.388
I...I...

32:35.431 --> 32:38.347
I d-- I don't suppose
there's anything I can...do

32:38.391 --> 32:42.351
to convince you to stay?

32:42.395 --> 32:43.962
Support for the boys.

32:44.005 --> 32:46.355
No. I'm sorry.
The decision's been made.

32:48.488 --> 32:52.057
Um, my -- hmm...

32:52.100 --> 32:55.147
...head of trauma
is still in surgery

32:55.190 --> 32:58.498
and could need
months of recovery,

32:58.541 --> 33:02.154
uh, so can you at least give me
until he's well?

33:02.197 --> 33:04.895
I mean, at this rate,
I'm hemorrhaging surgeons.

33:04.939 --> 33:06.506
I just can't.

33:09.161 --> 33:11.772
I truly am sorry.

33:11.815 --> 33:13.687
I've loved my time here.

33:16.516 --> 33:18.822
But I got to do
what's best for my family.

33:20.389 --> 33:22.565
I'll hand off my cases.

33:22.609 --> 33:24.611
This will be my last shift.

33:28.180 --> 33:29.746
I'm sorry.

33:29.790 --> 33:39.365
♪♪

33:39.408 --> 33:49.070
♪♪

33:57.557 --> 34:00.255
So, are we celebrating
with drinks at Joe's

34:00.299 --> 34:01.778
or pajamas in bed?

34:03.171 --> 34:04.433
Woman: Grey-Sloan Memorial.
How can I...

34:04.477 --> 34:06.174
What --
What was that look for?

34:09.482 --> 34:11.179
"Take in the miracle."

34:13.094 --> 34:15.662
You're a person
who takes in miracles.

34:15.705 --> 34:17.142
I didn't know that
about you.

34:17.185 --> 34:18.534
What, you don't?

34:18.578 --> 34:21.624
I take in science,
data, reason...

34:21.668 --> 34:22.886
calculated risk.

34:22.930 --> 34:24.627
And today, you jumped in

34:24.671 --> 34:27.108
and had my back
when I decided to leap.

34:27.152 --> 34:30.372
You were right there --
every stitch, every move.

34:30.416 --> 34:31.634
Meaning?

34:31.678 --> 34:34.594
Meaning we both
showed up.

34:34.637 --> 34:36.422
We were a team.

34:36.465 --> 34:39.425
Owen and Teddy and Hayes,
they're alive,

34:39.468 --> 34:41.731
and they kept
that heart alive.

34:41.775 --> 34:44.212
The two of us,
we were a team.

34:44.256 --> 34:46.084
We gave that boy a heart.

34:46.127 --> 34:48.216
So call it a miracle --

34:48.260 --> 34:51.480
Or skill, precision,
hard work.

34:51.524 --> 34:52.960
Okay. Either way.

34:53.003 --> 34:55.919
That boy's brand-new heart
is beating in his chest.

34:57.965 --> 35:00.185
His heart is beating
in his chest.

35:01.664 --> 35:03.101
Hmm.

35:07.148 --> 35:08.758
Pajamas.

35:08.802 --> 35:10.673
We're definitely celebrating
with pajamas.

35:13.937 --> 35:15.809
[ Siren wails in distance ]

35:17.376 --> 35:19.421
Nick: Meredith!

35:19.465 --> 35:22.207
Hi.
I thought
you'd never get here.

35:22.250 --> 35:24.339
What do you mean?
I'm right on time.I know.

35:24.383 --> 35:25.906
How you doing?

35:25.949 --> 35:27.299
Bad day, huh?
Yeah.

35:27.342 --> 35:29.127
What's up?

35:29.170 --> 35:30.954
My friend got into
a car accident.

35:30.998 --> 35:32.608
Oh, no.
Yeah.

35:32.652 --> 35:35.045
My other friend quit.

35:35.089 --> 35:36.612
Oh, no.

35:36.656 --> 35:38.832
And then my favorite resident
flamed out.

35:38.875 --> 35:41.095
Geez. This place really falls
apart without you, doesn't it?

35:41.139 --> 35:42.705
[ Chuckles ]

35:42.749 --> 35:44.533
Well, I got us
a reservation

35:44.577 --> 35:47.406
at a nice restaurant
not too far from here.

35:47.449 --> 35:49.277
I thought that might be
your reaction,

35:49.321 --> 35:51.497
so I also got a hotel
with amazing room service.

35:51.540 --> 35:53.325
Yes, better.

35:53.368 --> 35:55.370
Much better.

35:55.414 --> 35:57.503
[ Indistinct conversations ]

35:57.546 --> 35:59.940
[ Sighs ]

35:59.983 --> 36:01.246
Hey.

36:01.289 --> 36:03.117
Hi.

36:03.161 --> 36:04.597
[ Sighs ]
Fries?

36:04.640 --> 36:07.077
Yeah. Please.

36:07.121 --> 36:08.862
♪ Strangely, there's
nobody else around ♪

36:08.905 --> 36:10.516
How did the surgery go?

36:10.559 --> 36:14.389
Uh, well, the patient has
a long road to recovery,

36:14.433 --> 36:17.436
but he's alive
and he's not paralyzed.

36:17.479 --> 36:19.873
And he is my ex-husband.

36:19.916 --> 36:23.137
And, uh, the surgeon
who operated with me

36:23.181 --> 36:26.053
is my son's father,

36:26.096 --> 36:30.666
so, you know...
family reunion.
Got it.

36:32.059 --> 36:33.800
Oh. Got it.

36:33.843 --> 36:36.455
So he cleared the gallery
because I came in?

36:36.498 --> 36:37.934
He saw us kissing.

36:41.024 --> 36:42.591
My life, uh, is...

36:46.029 --> 36:47.161
...messy.

36:48.510 --> 36:50.251
And I would
totally understand

36:50.295 --> 36:52.645
if you don't want anything
to do with that mess.

36:52.688 --> 36:54.560
♪ Hear your voice

36:57.127 --> 37:01.393
Tell me, is your type
always hot, square-jawed men?

37:01.436 --> 37:03.612
Lately,
it appears my type

37:03.656 --> 37:06.615
is hot, square-jawed you.

37:08.138 --> 37:09.749
Touché.

37:09.792 --> 37:11.664
What about you?
Do you have a type?

37:11.707 --> 37:14.580
No, but I'm sharing my fries.
That's not a small thing.

37:17.496 --> 37:18.975
[ Cellphone chimes ]

37:19.019 --> 37:22.022
♪ I still see you

37:24.024 --> 37:27.462
♪ The sunlight on your face
in my rearview ♪

37:27.506 --> 37:28.420
Is that your kid?

37:28.463 --> 37:29.856
That's Scout.

37:29.899 --> 37:31.640
His dad sends
a goodnight photo of him

37:31.684 --> 37:34.556
every night that he has him.

37:34.600 --> 37:36.384
Even if we're fighting.

37:38.343 --> 37:39.779
He's a good man.

37:39.822 --> 37:41.911
I hate that
I broke his heart,

37:41.955 --> 37:46.089
and I hate that he made me
break it all over again.

37:46.133 --> 37:51.617
♪♪

37:51.660 --> 37:52.966
You want me
to grab you a drink?

37:53.009 --> 37:54.837
Yes. [ Chuckles ]

37:54.881 --> 37:57.144
But, no,
because I don't drink.

37:57.187 --> 38:02.105
♪♪

38:02.149 --> 38:07.197
♪♪

38:07.241 --> 38:08.590
Thank you.

38:08.634 --> 38:10.636
♪ When you go away

38:10.679 --> 38:13.116
♪ I still see you

38:20.036 --> 38:21.777
Thank you.

38:28.262 --> 38:30.220
I don't want to feel
all this again.

38:33.398 --> 38:34.616
Then don't.

38:35.661 --> 38:37.140
Helpful. Thank you.

38:37.184 --> 38:39.752
[ Chuckles ]
I'm saying, don't.

38:39.795 --> 38:42.798
I'm saying
life is hard enough,

38:42.842 --> 38:45.975
and sometimes on bad days,
we kill people

38:46.019 --> 38:48.891
and wash our hands
until they bleed.

38:48.935 --> 38:51.677
Maybe don't suffer
any more than you have to.

38:52.852 --> 38:54.070
Is it that easy?

38:55.637 --> 38:57.813
Maybe.

38:57.857 --> 39:01.861
Amelia is a good mom
and a great surgeon

39:01.904 --> 39:03.471
and a decent human being,
I guess,

39:03.515 --> 39:06.605
but she doesn't want
what you want.

39:06.648 --> 39:09.869
And you -- you are...

39:09.912 --> 39:12.132
Atticus Lincoln.[ Chuckles ]

39:12.175 --> 39:16.397
You are the best ortho surgeon,
the best bartender,

39:16.441 --> 39:17.833
the best father I know,

39:17.877 --> 39:21.315
and you're also just, like,
really hot.

39:21.359 --> 39:23.404
[ Chuckles ]
I'm serious!

39:23.448 --> 39:25.406
You're the hottest guy
that everyone knows.

39:25.450 --> 39:29.323
Let's just not pretend
that that's not true.

39:29.367 --> 39:32.021
There are other women
who would...

39:32.065 --> 39:34.589
love to love you, Link.

39:35.895 --> 39:37.287
I ama catch.

39:37.331 --> 39:38.941
[ Laughs ]
There's no denying it.

39:38.985 --> 39:40.726
[ Laughs ]

39:45.295 --> 39:46.949
You already mourned her.

39:48.734 --> 39:50.518
You already suffered,
so maybe just...

39:53.869 --> 39:56.045
...don't suffer anymore.

39:56.089 --> 40:03.313
♪♪

40:03.357 --> 40:05.446
♪ There's nothing left to say

40:05.490 --> 40:08.231
♪ No breath in your lungs

40:08.275 --> 40:11.017
♪♪

40:11.060 --> 40:12.801
♪ Standing in flames

40:12.845 --> 40:15.108
♪ The wreckage of us

40:15.151 --> 40:17.632
♪♪

40:17.676 --> 40:19.591
♪ Caught in this war

40:19.634 --> 40:21.331
This is a bad idea.

40:21.375 --> 40:22.811
Is it?

40:22.855 --> 40:26.467
♪ It's a dangerous love

40:26.511 --> 40:29.514
♪ Mmm-mm

40:29.557 --> 40:32.430
♪♪

40:32.473 --> 40:39.698
♪ Ooh-ooh

40:39.741 --> 40:45.747
♪ Ooh-ooh

40:47.880 --> 40:49.795
♪ There's nothing left to say

40:49.838 --> 40:52.188
♪ Your heart turned to stone

40:52.232 --> 40:55.017
♪♪

40:55.061 --> 40:57.019
♪ It's too late to save

40:57.063 --> 41:01.284
♪ You're already gone

41:01.328 --> 41:02.982
Meredith:
Recent studies suggest

41:03.025 --> 41:04.940
that when we experience
physical sensations

41:04.984 --> 41:07.116
related to intense emotions,

41:07.160 --> 41:09.423
it comes back
to the vagus nerve.

41:09.467 --> 41:11.556
♪♪

41:11.599 --> 41:14.123
♪ Mmm-mm

41:14.167 --> 41:16.735
[ Elevator bell dings,
doors close ]

41:16.778 --> 41:23.002
♪ Ooh-ooh

41:24.351 --> 41:26.440
♪ Ooh-ooh

41:26.484 --> 41:28.398
We think of the pain
of a broken heart

41:28.442 --> 41:30.183
as being
outside of our control.

41:30.226 --> 41:31.663
[ Siren chirps ]

41:31.706 --> 41:38.800
♪ Ooh-ooh

41:38.844 --> 41:44.414
♪ Ooh-ooh

41:44.458 --> 41:49.028
♪♪

41:49.071 --> 41:53.598
But science suggests that
if we laugh instead of cry...

41:53.641 --> 41:57.906
if we sing instead of ache...

41:57.950 --> 42:00.909
we might just heal faster.

42:00.953 --> 42:08.351
♪ Ooh-ooh

42:08.395 --> 42:14.880
♪ Ooh-ooh

42:14.923 --> 42:17.796
[ Groaning ] Ahh.

42:17.839 --> 42:21.800
Okay, okay. Hey.
Okay. Here.

42:21.843 --> 42:23.628
Press this if you need
some more, okay?

42:23.671 --> 42:25.586
[ Beep ]
Yep.

42:25.630 --> 42:27.196
Give it a second.

42:27.240 --> 42:28.589
Okay.

42:28.633 --> 42:30.765
[ Breathing heavily ]

42:30.809 --> 42:33.463
Okay. Okay. Phew.

42:33.507 --> 42:35.378
The surgery?

42:35.422 --> 42:36.510
It went well.

42:36.554 --> 42:38.425
I'll walk?
Yes.

42:38.468 --> 42:40.079
It'll take time, but yes.

42:40.122 --> 42:43.343
Ohh.

42:43.386 --> 42:46.476
Bailey just stopped by
to check on you.

42:46.520 --> 42:49.001
She told me
that Hayes quit.

42:49.044 --> 42:51.743
Says he wants to
go back to Ireland.

42:53.788 --> 42:55.050
[ Sighs ]

42:55.094 --> 42:56.965
What happened
in that car, Owen?

42:57.009 --> 42:59.185
Of course,
when we're hurting...

42:59.228 --> 43:00.926
What are you
not telling me?

43:00.969 --> 43:03.319
...sometimes it's just easier
to keep hurting

43:03.363 --> 43:05.365
than to try to heal.

43:29.607 --> 43:37.745
♪♪

43:37.789 --> 43:46.058
♪♪

43:46.101 --> 43:54.240
♪♪
